<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1413,2015]" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis box="[199,421,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Description, female</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[583,672,1485,1511]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.9" pageId="6" pageNumber="127" unit="mm" value="7.9">7.9 mm</quantity>
, fore wing length 
<quantity box="[879,969,1484,1511]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="127" unit="mm" value="5.1">5.1 mm</quantity>
. Strikingly bicolored (
<figureCitation box="[1223,1314,1485,1511]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1515,1540]" captionTargetBox="[224,1362,273,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[224,1362,273,1491]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML). A. Habitus, lateral. B. Head, anterior. C. Antenna. Green arrow = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = longitudinal carina on abdominal tergum 9; yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; white arrows = longitudinal lines on frons; blue arrow = notch in ventral transverse frontal carina." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887932" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887932/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
), head and prothorax predominantly reddish brown, except for black coronal teeth and mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[1123,1211,1521,1547]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1515,1540]" captionTargetBox="[224,1362,273,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[224,1362,273,1491]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML). A. Habitus, lateral. B. Head, anterior. C. Antenna. Green arrow = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = longitudinal carina on abdominal tergum 9; yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; white arrows = longitudinal lines on frons; blue arrow = notch in ventral transverse frontal carina." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887932" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887932/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); remainder of body predominantly dark brown to black, except for mid and hind coxae and femora, and tergum 10 and cercus, which are reddish brown. Fore wing with pterostigma and venation mostly dark brown, except within hyaline areas (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1901,1926]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML).A. Head and thorax, dorsal. B. Fore wing. C.Abdomen and hind leg, dorsal. Yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; blue arrow = occipital carina; green arrows = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = vein cu-a; violet arrows = pegs on hind tibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887934" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887934/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
); two large infuscate areas with dense setation present, basal area extends from wing base to just proximally of pterostigma, distal area separated from proximal by hyaline band, extends across wing from just proximal to vein 2r-rs to some distance from tip, leaving tip of wing hyaline, boundary between distal infuscate area and hyaline tip wavy; hind wing vein R dark brown, venation otherwise light brown, some longitudinal veins darker in the basal part, single weakly infuscate area extends from R–Rs fork to tip of wing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1413,2015]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,152,251]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Head</emphasis>
. Ocellar corona narrow, distance between median ocellus and lateral coronal teeth approximately equal to width of ocellus; dorsalmost coronal teeth situated dorsal to lateral ocelli, small and staggered in regular pattern several teeth wide (
<figureCitation box="[367,458,1881,1907]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1515,1540]" captionTargetBox="[224,1362,273,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[224,1362,273,1491]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML). A. Habitus, lateral. B. Head, anterior. C. Antenna. Green arrow = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = longitudinal carina on abdominal tergum 9; yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; white arrows = longitudinal lines on frons; blue arrow = notch in ventral transverse frontal carina." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887932" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887932/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Figs 4B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[470,507,1880,1907]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1901,1926]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML).A. Head and thorax, dorsal. B. Fore wing. C.Abdomen and hind leg, dorsal. Yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; blue arrow = occipital carina; green arrows = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = vein cu-a; violet arrows = pegs on hind tibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887934" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887934/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">5A</figureCitation>
), medially separated by narrow longitudinal groove. Dorsal transverse, median and lateral frontal carinae absent. Setae on frons not conspicuously flattened. Ventral transverse frontal carina with very prominent median notch (
<figureCitation box="[443,532,1953,1979]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1515,1540]" captionTargetBox="[224,1362,273,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[224,1362,273,1491]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML). A. Habitus, lateral. B. Head, anterior. C. Antenna. Green arrow = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = longitudinal carina on abdominal tergum 9; yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; white arrows = longitudinal lines on frons; blue arrow = notch in ventral transverse frontal carina." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887932" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887932/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); median longitudinal line extends from notch to ocellar corona, flanked by two diverging sublateral lines that do not extend as far dorsal as median one, all lines faint. Postocular carina absent, occipital carina well developed (
<figureCitation box="[525,617,152,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1901,1926]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML).A. Head and thorax, dorsal. B. Fore wing. C.Abdomen and hind leg, dorsal. Yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; blue arrow = occipital carina; green arrows = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = vein cu-a; violet arrows = pegs on hind tibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887934" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887934/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
), occipital concavity absent; setation on gena weakly developed except ventrally lateral to carina laterally delimiting the subantennal groove. Frons, vertex, and gena areolate. Antenna slender, antennomere 9 not swollen subapically, antennomere 10 approximately 3× as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[1273,1363,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1515,1540]" captionTargetBox="[224,1362,273,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[224,1362,273,1491]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML). A. Habitus, lateral. B. Head, anterior. C. Antenna. Green arrow = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = longitudinal carina on abdominal tergum 9; yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; white arrows = longitudinal lines on frons; blue arrow = notch in ventral transverse frontal carina." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887932" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887932/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887932" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3887932" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887932/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="128" startId="7.[151,250,1515,1540]" targetBox="[224,1362,273,1490]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1515,1648]" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,277,1515,1540]" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Vilhelmsen, 2020" authorityName="Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2020" box="[286,553,1516,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Orussidae" genus="Ophrynopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufocephalus" status="n. sp.">
