</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[562,620,1516,1539]" pageId="7" pageNumber="128" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female holotype (NHML). A. Habitus, lateral. B. Head, anterior. C. Antenna. Green arrow = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = longitudinal carina on abdominal tergum 9; yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; white arrows = longitudinal lines on frons; blue arrow = notch in ventral transverse frontal carina.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1694,2045]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,152,251]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="129" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1694,1720]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum with very distinct transverse carina anterodorsally, carina projecting anteriorly and with prominent notch medially (
<figureCitation box="[457,551,1730,1757]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1515,1540]" captionTargetBox="[224,1362,273,1490]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[224,1362,273,1491]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML). A. Habitus, lateral. B. Head, anterior. C. Antenna. Green arrow = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = longitudinal carina on abdominal tergum 9; yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; white arrows = longitudinal lines on frons; blue arrow = notch in ventral transverse frontal carina." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887932" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887932/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Figs 4A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[563,601,1730,1757]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1901,1926]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML).A. Head and thorax, dorsal. B. Fore wing. C.Abdomen and hind leg, dorsal. Yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; blue arrow = occipital carina; green arrows = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = vein cu-a; violet arrows = pegs on hind tibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887934" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887934/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">5A</figureCitation>
); pronotum not longer laterally than medially in dorsal view, areolate dorsally, smooth with scattered punctures on anterior face. Fore femur with distinct carina ventrally. Mesoscutum only slightly shorter than broad, areolate, longitudinal carina absent, pilosity indistinct (
<figureCitation box="[1099,1191,1802,1829]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1901,1926]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML).A. Head and thorax, dorsal. B. Fore wing. C.Abdomen and hind leg, dorsal. Yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; blue arrow = occipital carina; green arrows = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = vein cu-a; violet arrows = pegs on hind tibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887934" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887934/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
); mesoscuto-scutellar sulcus distinct, with deep rectangular pits, axillar flanges distinctly carinate, rectangular; mesoscutellum areolate, with indistinct lateral margins, posteriorly parallel with anterior margin of metanotum for some distance. Mesopleuron with distinct mesepisternal carina, areolate dorsally except for small glabrous/imbricate depression with few large pits posterodorsally, finely punctate ventrally, with silvery pilosity only ventrally. Metanotum areolate with median and lateral longitudinal carinae not discernible. Metepisternum areolate except for small glabrous area in middle. Hind coxa laterally striate, without pilosity; hind femur with small denticles ventrally, but no carina; hind tibia dorsally with pegs in two rows (
<figureCitation box="[576,665,152,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1901,1926]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML).A. Head and thorax, dorsal. B. Fore wing. C.Abdomen and hind leg, dorsal. Yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; blue arrow = occipital carina; green arrows = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = vein cu-a; violet arrows = pegs on hind tibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887934" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887934/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
), outer row with eleven pegs, and with longitudinal carina laterally; apical hind tibial spurs of approximately equal length, short, less than half apical tibial width. Fore wing with vein cu-a inserting on Cu approximately 1/3 from proximal end of cell M (
<figureCitation box="[933,1021,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1901,1926]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[241,1346,273,1876]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Ophrynopus rufocephalus n. sp., female holotype (NHML).A. Head and thorax, dorsal. B. Fore wing. C.Abdomen and hind leg, dorsal. Yellow arrow = groove between dorsalmost coronal teeth; blue arrow = occipital carina; green arrows = transverse pronotal carina; red arrow = vein cu-a; violet arrows = pegs on hind tibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887934" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887934/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="129">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
